com.rapidminer.extension.indatabase.operator

Interface NestedOperator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNestedOperator, AggregateOperator, DistinctOperator, FilterOperator, GenerateAttributes, JoinOperator, Multiply, RenameOperator, RetrieveOperator, SampleOperator, SelectOperator, SortOperator, StoreOperator, UnionOperator

    public interface NestedOperator
    Common interface for the nested Indatabase operators. All nested Indatabase operator must implement this interface. Some methods should be called in specific point of the code, as outlined below in the method descriptions.

      • checkIsInIndatabaseNest

        default java.util.List<com.rapidminer.operator.ports.quickfix.QuickFix> checkIsInIndatabaseNest(boolean applyAutoFixes)
        Checks, if the operator is inside an InDatabase Nest operator, if not, either an autofix (replace with non-indatabase equivalent) or an error with quickfix (remove operator) is generated.
        Parameters:
        applyAutoFixes - do apply the auto fixes automatically, or return them at the end of the method in a list.
        Returns:
        list of not applied autofixes, if applyAutoFixes is true, this list is always empty, otherwise may not emtpy.
